    <svcsection id="EGES265-Section12" svcsectype="enginesec" division="engine" date="03/25/04">
        <title>Fuel System</title>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The low-pressure fuel system consists of components carrying fuel from the fuel tank to the fuel
                    inlet ports of the injectors. The following figure illustrates
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f2651201" appearance="hottext">low-pressure fuel flow</hotlnk>
                    from the fuel filter (from tank) to each of the injectors.
                </para>
                <figure id="f2651201" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figH31/H31002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                    <caption>Low-pressure fuel system</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder head</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector assembly (6)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel rail (cast in intake manifold)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Transfer pump outlet tube assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel supply pump</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Primer pump assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain valve</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Drain valve (strainer)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Transfer pump inlet tube assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter module</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel piping from tank(s)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fitting (service port)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet ports (4)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>The
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f2651202.5" appearance="hottext">high-pressure oil system</hotlnk>
                    consists of components carrying oil from the front cover reservoir to the oil inlet at the top of
                    each fuel injector. It is at the injector where hydraulic force on each fuel charge is magnified
                    seven times.
                </para>
                <figure id="f2651202.5" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figH11/H11001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                    <caption>High-pressure oil system</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil manifold</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector assembly (6)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure pump assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Oil inlet from front cover reservoir</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure hose</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Oil inlet from high-pressure oil manifold</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Oil outlet (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet ports (4)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
